# How to build and run rvoffload on emulator

Create a share folder for qemu to mount

## Build rvoffload
branch: dev/yunh/iree-demo-with-refactor-device (will merged into sifive-dev after review)

git clone git@github.com:sifive/rvoffload.git
cd rvoffload
git submodule update --init
rvoffload runtime
cmake -B build-runtime-riscv -DRVO_LOG_DISABLE=ON -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../cmake/riscv.toolchain.cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=build-runtime-riscv/install .
cmake --build build-runtime-riscv -j64 --target install

The runtime/build-runtime-riscv/install/lib64/librvo.so should be copied to the qemu share folder.

## rvoffload device daemon
cmake -B build-device-riscv -DRVO_LOG_DISABLE=ON -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../cmake/riscv.toolchain.cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=build-device-riscv/install .
cmake --build build-device-riscv -j64 --target install

The device/build-device-riscv/install/bin/moray_daemonshould be copied to qemu share folder.


## buildroot
git clone git@github.com:buildroot/buildroot.git
make qemu_riscv64_virt_defconfig

Modified these config in .config
# BR2_LINUX_KERNEL is not set
BR2_TARGET_ROOTFS_CPIO=y
BR2_TARGET_ROOTFS_CPIO_FULL=y
# BR2_PACKAGE_HOST_QEMU is not set
build
make
The toolchain is under output/host/bin/ and the cpio file is output/images/rootfs.cpio
linux-private
git clone git@github.com:sifive/linux-private.git -b dev/vincentc/v6.16-northstar
cd linux-private

make ARCH=riscv defconfig
make ARCH=riscv CROSS_COMPILE=riscv64-unknown-linux-gnu- CONFIG_INITRAMFS_SOURCE=<buildroot>/output/images/rootfs.cpio -j20


The kernel image is build/arch/riscv/boot/Image

## sifive_xm_accel
Apply this patch before building: /nfs/teams/sw/share/yunh/share/rvoffload_tinyllama_test_material/sifive_xm_sync_memcpy.diff
git clone git@github.com:sifive/sifive_xm_accel.git
cd sifive_xm_accel

make HOST=riscv DEV=riscv CROSS_COMPILE=riscv64-linux- KDIR=/scratch/yunh/projects/rvoffload/linux-private/build emulator_sock test
make HOST=riscv DEV=riscv CROSS_COMPILE=riscv64-linux- KDIR=/scratch/yunh/projects/rvoffload/linux-private/build install

The modules are under bins/modules .
